ce:section.ce:para:
The as-prepared alkali lignin was subjected to a dynamic solvent-fractionation procedure capable of recovering its three fractions, and the structural characterizations of refined lignin fractions (i.e., L50, L100 and LR) were conducted via a series of techniques (
                           supporting information
                        ). The hydrothermal treatment of lignin acidolysis filtrate was conducted to acquire the species of FCDs. Afterwards, the acidolysis-treated leftover lignin are transformed through a stepwise route of solvothermal engineering followed by dichloromethane/water extraction to collect the water-phase (WCDs) and dichloromethane-phase (DCDs) detached lignin carbon dots (LCDs). We also evaluated the structural features, fluorescent sensing, and solid-state luminescent composite film of using various fluorescence LCDs (
                           supporting information
                        ).
